The paper deals with the Restricted Isometry Property (RIP) which is a concept in information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also has applications in statistical learning, compressed sensing, and random matrix theory, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper investigates the effectiveness of word vector embeddings in natural language processing, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
